Hi everyone,

Our programmers are trying to make our robot turn to face a April tag when the drive team presses a button to assist with aiming for launching notes. We’re getting this setup and have managed to make the bot turn using the DriveTrain Drive Request and have moved on to the next step of implementing the apriltag detection with our Limelight 3.

We are just trying to turn right now when we see an April tag for troubleshooting purposes.

We’re using the LimelightHelper’s class using the TV variable for the testing right now to see if we see any April tag. In our class we have the tv value printed to the DriverStation to confirm that we see or do not see an April tag and this is working as intended. Once we actually implement the boolean tv into an if statement that would make the robot turn when we see an April tag, the drive request does not run.

We have added another debug statement into the if statement reporting to the DriverStation ‘IF STATEMENT’ if it runs, and it does when tv is true. It will just not process the drive request for some reason. We’re unable to figure out this reasoning and need help with this issue, if we put a different boolean in the if statement instead of tv the code runs fine.

We’re using the Phoenix Tuner X swerve generator. You can find our code at our GitHub, the if statement thats causing us issues is Line 54.

It looks like you are setting the priority tag ID to be 18 on line 48. I would first test it without setting this, as the getTV() function only returns true if that specific tag is visible. Also, for aligning to speaker, you should be using red/blue alliance’s speaker tags, which should be 3/4 and 7/8 if I remember correctly, not tag 18.

On another note, it might be worth putting the limelight’s hostname into the first arg on the Limelighthelper functions. I’m pretty sure it should default to limelight if the field is blank, but it might be worth checking out.
